11#[cfg(feature = "log")]
12use log::{info, warn};
13
14#[derive(Clone, Debug, Deserialize, Getters, Hash)]
15#[non_exhaustive]
16pub struct StickerPack {
17	pub(crate) name: String,
18	pub(crate) title: String,
19	pub(crate) stickers: Vec<Sticker>
20}
21
22impl StickerPack {
23	/// Request a stickerpack by its name.
24	pub async fn get(name: &str, tg_config: &Config) -> Result<Self, Error> {
25		let mut pack: Result<Self, _> = tg_get(tg_config, "getStickerSet", [("name", name)]).await;
26		if let Ok(ref mut pack) = pack {
27			for (i, sticker) in pack.stickers.iter_mut().enumerate() {
28				sticker.pack_name = pack.name.clone();
29				sticker.positon = i;
30			}
31		}
32		pack
33	}
34
35	/// Import this pack to matrix.
36	///
37	/// This function can partially fail, when the import of some stickers has failed (for example sticker use webm format, or reqwest has failed).
38	/// Because of this, the result error type inculde the successful part of the Stickerpack
39	/// and a tupple with the postion of failed stickers and the associated error.
40	pub async fn import<'a, D>(
41		&self,
42		tg_config: &Config,
43		matrix_config: &matrix::Config,
44		advance_config: &ImportConfig<'a, D>
45	) -> Result<matrix::stickerpack::StickerPack, (matrix::stickerpack::StickerPack, Vec<(usize, Error)>)>
46	where
47		D: Database
48	{
49		#[cfg(feature = "log")]
50		if log::log_enabled!(log::Level::Info) {
51			info!(
52				"import Telegram stickerpack {:?}({})    {{{} Stickers}}",
53				self.title,
54				self.name,
55				self.stickers.len()
56			);
57		}
58
59		let stickers_import_futures = self
60			.stickers
61			.iter()
62			.map(|f| f.import(tg_config, matrix_config, advance_config));
63		let stickers = join_all(stickers_import_futures).await;
64
65		let mut ok_stickers = Vec::new();
66		let mut err_stickers = Vec::new();
67		for (i, sticker) in stickers.into_iter().enumerate() {
68			match sticker {
69				Ok(value) => ok_stickers.push(value),
70				Err(err) => err_stickers.push((i, err))
71			}
72		}
73
74		let stickerpack = matrix::stickerpack::StickerPack {
75			title: self.title.clone(),
76			id: format!("tg_name_{}", self.name),
77			tg_pack: Some((&self).to_owned().into()),
78			stickers: ok_stickers
79		};
80		#[cfg(feature = "log")]
81		if stickerpack.stickers.is_empty() {
82			warn!("imported pack {} is empty", self.name);
83		}
84		if err_stickers.is_empty() {
85			Ok(stickerpack)
86		} else {
87			Err((stickerpack, err_stickers))
88		}
89	}
90}
91
92/// Convert telegram stickerpack url to pack name.
93///
94/// The url must start with `https://t.me/addstickers/`, `t.me/addstickers/` or
95/// `tg://addstickers?set=`.
96pub fn pack_url_to_name(url: &str) -> Result<&str, InvalidPackUrl> {
97	url.strip_prefix("https://t.me/addstickers/")
98		.or_else(|| url.strip_prefix("t.me/addstickers/"))
99		.or_else(|| url.strip_prefix("tg://addstickers?set="))
100		.ok_or_else(|| InvalidPackUrl(url.to_owned()))
101}

103#[cfg(test)]
104mod tests {
105
106	use super::{ImportConfig, StickerPack};
107	use crate::{database::DummyDatabase, image::AnimationFormat};
108	#[cfg(feature = "lottie")]
109	use lottieconv::Rgba;
110	use std::env;
111
112	async fn import(pack: &str, animation_format: Option<AnimationFormat>) {
113		let matrix_config = crate::matrix::Config {
114			homeserver_url: "none".to_owned(),
115			user: "none".to_owned(),
116			access_token: "none".to_owned()
117		};
118		let tg_config = crate::tg::Config {
119			bot_key: env::var("TG_BOT_KEY").expect("environment variables TG_BOT_KEY is not set")
120		};
121		let pack = StickerPack::get(pack, &tg_config).await.unwrap();
122		let mut import_config = ImportConfig::<DummyDatabase> {
123			database: None,
124			dry_run: true,
125			..Default::default()
126		};
127		if let Some(animation_format) = animation_format {
128			import_config.animation_format = animation_format;
129		} else {
130			import_config.keep_webm = true;
131			import_config.keep_lottie = true;
132		}
133		let pack = pack.import(&tg_config, &matrix_config, &import_config).await.unwrap();
134		for sticker in pack.stickers {
135			let mimetype = sticker.image.meta_data.mimetype;
136			if let Some(animation_format) = animation_format {
137				match animation_format {
138					#[cfg(feature = "lottie")]
139					AnimationFormat::Gif { .. } => assert_eq!(mimetype, "image/gif"),
140					AnimationFormat::Webp => assert_eq!(mimetype, "image/webp")
141				}
142			} else {
143				assert!(mimetype == "image/lottie" || mimetype == "video/webm");
144			}
145		}
146	}
